  "texts": [
    "See Cronin v. J.B.E.",
    "Olson Corp., 501 P.2d 1153, 1162 (Cal. 1972).",
    "36 Product Liability Directive, article 4.",
    "In the EU, the definition of a defect is determined by the consumer-expectation test, which considers whether a product fails to meet the safety expectations the public is entitled to, considering all relevant circumstances.",
    "37 While the producer can be considered negligent for selling a product that does not meet legitimate consumer expectations (Reimann, 2003a, 776-777), the test does not assess defects by comparing a product's social benefits and costs (Wuyts, 2014)."
  ]
}